OL,6,FCllr John Lancaster said at Thursday's
OL,7,Fmeeting: "Clearly we have a
OL,8,Fresponsibility to the people who live
OL,9,Faround the Bay, the people who use it,
OL,10,Fbusinesses that want to be there, so
OL,11,Fsurely there has to be some sort of
OL,12,Fpressure from yourselves (council
OL,13,Fofficers) to work with the likes of
OL,14,FNRW (Natural Resources Wales) and
OL,15,FWelsh Water to address it."
OL,17,FThe Cardiff Harbour Authority (CHA)
OL,18,Fpublishes a daily Cardiff Bay water
OL,19,Fquality monitoring report on its
OL,20,Fwebsite.
